@@TJvSpacer.SetBounds
Summary
  Sets the spacing object's boundary properties all at once.
Description
  Use SetBounds to change all of the control’s boundary properties at once. SetBounds uses the Spacing
  property to determine the actual new height or width of the spacing object.
Parameters
  ALeft   - Specifies the horizontal coordinate of the left edge of the spacing object relative to 
            its parent. 
  ATop    - Specifies the vertical coordinate of the top left edge of the spacing object relative to
            its parent.
  AWidth  - Specifies the horizontal size of the spacing object or form in pixels.
  AHeight - Specifies the vertical size of the spacing object in pixels.
See Also
  Spacing
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpacer.Spacing
Summary
  Determines the size of the spacing object.
Description
  Use Spacing in combination with property Align to set the size of the spacing object. If Align equals
  alTop or alBottom then Spacing determines the height of the spacing object. If Align equals alLeft or
  alRight then Spacing determines the width of the spacing object.
See Also
  SetBounds
